It's marked "Not yet implemented" at http://manual.qooxdoo.org/current/pages/development/api_jsdoc_ref.html#lint and I haven't found any bug referencing "ignoreJsdocKey".
The usecase, as it seems to me, is inclusion of external libraries into qooxdoo app build, like in qx.bom.Template, qx.bom.Selector, etc.
Recently I played with JsZip library which uses incompatible JSDoc syntax, so it bloats the generator console with many warning messages which are currently no way to suppress. Hopefully parsing attempts happen only on modification, so subsequent builds go as usual.
*** Bug 7504 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***

Created attachment 1277 test app
Can't verify. Console is getting bloated in the same way with "Unable to parse JSDoc entry: ..." when ``@lint ignoreJsdocKey()`` presents.

Because scoping of ``@lint`` is different from ``@ignore``'s it can be a little confusing from the spot (i.e. no file "global" scope). It can deserve a memo in the [1]. Since an external library can be wrapped in anonymous function, if not already, and @lint affects it all, the rest is fine, thanks :-)

(In reply to comment #5) > Because scoping of ``@lint`` is different from ``@ignore``'s it can be a little confusing from the spot > (i.e. no file "global" scope). It can deserve a memo in the [1].
Their scoping is actually the same so the behavior of @lint in this case is weird. I'll look into that ...
Closed all bugs already shipped with a release.
